Sentencas: The impact of a nanostructured NiO/yttria-stabilized zirconia (NiO/YSZ) and NiO/gadolinia-doped ceria (NiO/GDC) anode functional layers on low-and intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) performance is investigated.
Titulo: Reactive co-sputter deposition of nanostructured cermet anodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: NiO/YSZ and NiO/GDC thin films were reactively sputter-deposited by pulsed direct current magnetron sputtering from the Ni, Zr-Y, and Ce-Gd targets onto commercial NiO/YSZ substrates.
Titulo: Reactive co-sputter deposition of nanostructured cermet anodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Anode-supported SOFCs based on magnetron sputtered YSZ and GDC electrolytes (similar to 4 mu m) with and without the nanostructured anode layers are fabricated.
Titulo: Reactive co-sputter deposition of nanostructured cermet anodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A direct comparison of the YSZ- and GDC-based SOFCs in temperature range of 600-800 and 400-600 degrees C is made.
Titulo: Reactive co-sputter deposition of nanostructured cermet anodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The performance of cells with the nanostructured anode layers significantly increases as compared to that of the cell without it, especially at lower temperatures.
Titulo: Reactive co-sputter deposition of nanostructured cermet anodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Increase of cells performance was achieved by reduction of the total area-specific resistance by 26-30%.
Titulo: Reactive co-sputter deposition of nanostructured cermet anodes for solid oxide fuel cells
